  "prompt": "Last year my score for CAT was around 40 percentile. What should I do to score > 90  percentile this year?",
  "response": "To improve your CAT percentile from 40 to over 90, you'll need a comprehensive and strategic approach:\n\n1. Diagnostic Analysis\n- Analyze your previous CAT attempt\n- Identify weak sections and topics\n- Understand your strengths and weaknesses\n\n2. Preparation Strategy\n- Create a structured study plan\n- Allocate more time to weaker sections\n- Focus on fundamentals first\n- Practice consistently\n\n3. Quantitative Aptitude\n- Strengthen basic mathematics\n- Learn shortcut techniques\n- Practice problem-solving\n- Mock tests and previous year papers\n\n4. Verbal Ability\n- Improve reading comprehension\n- Expand vocabulary\n- Practice grammar\n- Read newspapers, magazines, novels\n\n5. Logical Reasoning\n- Solve puzzles and mock tests\n- Learn different reasoning techniques\n- Practice time management\n\n6. Mock Tests\n- Take 20-25 full-length mock tests\n- Analyze each mock test\n- Simulate exam conditions\n- Track performance improvements\n\n7. Time Management\n- Practice solving questions quickly\n- Learn to prioritize questions\n- Develop section-wise time allocation strategy\n\n8. Additional Resources\n- Coaching classes\n- Online study materials\n- Standard reference books\n- Video tutorials\n\nRemember: Consistent effort and smart preparation are key to significant improvement.",
